700028f-a.title: Bronx: 132nd Street (East) - Locust Avenue
700028f-a.text:
(1)
East 132nd Street (directly in front of power plant), north side,
from Locust Ave., to the East River (right), showing the power plant
of the Dnited Electric Light and Power Co. The New York, New Haven
and Hartford Railroad tracks appear on the left.
Aprul 12, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, from a slightly different angle.
April 12, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
